parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the airbag and seatbelt can lead to severe injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident, as well as cause loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: Airbag failure to deploy
seatbelt failure to lock
sudden stops
and unexpected braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Delayed Recall Repair for Airbag Defect
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in repairing the airbag defect can lead to continued risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Notification of recall
but parts are not available
and the manufacturer has exceeded a reasonable amount of time for the recall repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lack of explanation from the manufacturer and dealership can lead to uncertainty and concern about the safety of the vehicle.
symptoms: Unclear explanation of the problem
conflicting information from the manufacturer and dealership
and uncertainty about the safety of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The melting of the driver's side mirror can cause visibility issues, which can lead to accidents or near-misses, and also result in costly repairs.
symptoms: The driver's side mirror melts or becomes deformed
requiring replacement or repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the multi-information display, including the fuel gauge, can cause confusion and distraction while driving, leading to potential accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The multi-information display produces a blank screen or illegible text
often resolving on its own after a minute or two
but progressively getting worse over time.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden shattering of the sunroof can cause injury to occupants, damage to the vehicle, and potentially lead to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The sunroof shatters without any apparent reason or warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent loss of acceleration can cause accidents or near-misses, especially when merging or changing lanes, and can lead to a loss of confidence in the vehicle's performance.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to accelerate when the gas pedal is pressed
often occurring intermittently and without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended activation of the brakes can cause sudden stops, potentially leading to accidents, injuries, or damage to the vehicle. This issue can also lead to a loss of control, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The brakes engage automatically
even when there is no obstacle or traffic ahead
the brake light comes on
the vehicle beeps or makes a warning sound
the brakes slam on hard
a scraping or grinding noise is heard from the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brakes to hold the vehicle can cause it to move unexpectedly, potentially leading to accidents, injuries, or damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: The vehicle starts moving slowly when stopped at a traffic light or on the freeway
the brakes do not hold the vehicle in place
the driver must push harder on the brakes to stop the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster can cause the odometer and other essential gauges to malfunction, leading to a lack of critical information for the driver, which can increase the risk of accidents or stalling on the road.
symptoms: The odometer section of the dashboard fails to light up or turn on
the odometer flashes or turns on after a delay
the instrument cluster malfunctions or fails to display critical information.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Failure (Power Locks and Theft Alarm)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the power locks to malfunction, trapping the driver or passengers inside the vehicle, and the theft alarm to activate independently, which can lead to safety risks and inconvenience.
symptoms: The power lock system fails to open the doors
the theft alarm system activates independently
the doors lock and unlock independently while driving
the power locks fail to unlock the doors
trapping the driver or passengers.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the key to not go into the ignition, making it difficult or impossible to start the vehicle, which can lead to inconvenience and safety risks.
symptoms: The key does not go into the ignition
the vehicle will not turn off
the ignition system malfunctions or fails to function properly.
